  "question_id": "12f3a8d6-9a50-4bae-81c6-dbf8db8dd365",
  "short_text": "Square - 2",
  "content": "Write a program that reads a number `N` and prints a **Square** of `N` rows and `N` columns using numbers starting from **1**.\n\n```\n111\n222\n333\n```\n\n---\n\n#### Input\n\nThe input will be a single line containing an integer representing `N`.\n\n---\n\n#### Output\n\nThe output should be `N` rows containing numbers as a **Square** shown in the sample output.\n\n---\n\n#### Explanation\n\nFor example, if the given number is `N = 4`,\n\n- Print the numbers on **4** rows and **4** columns as shown in the given image.\n\n<Img imageSrc='https://assets.ccbp.in/frontend/content/programming-foundations/square-2.png' widthPercent='50'/>\n\nThe output should be,\n\n```\n1111\n2222\n3333\n4444\n```\n",
  "question_type": "CODING",
  "content_type": "MARKDOWN",
  "codes": [
    {
      "code_id": "60cd2620-33aa-40b6-8c6d-2eb911d4e9ff",
      "code_content": "number = int(input())\n\ncounter = 1\nwhile counter <= number:\n    row = str(counter) * number\n    print(row)\n    counter = counter + 1",
      "language": "PYTHON",
      "default_code": true
    }
  ],
